meanings: 입원에 관한 표현 It's not delicious, but it's healthful.

examples.korean: I don’t think I’ll be any good at tennis, but I’ll give it a try. 발음듣기 내가 테니스를 조금도 잘할 거라고는 생각하지 않지만 한번 시도는 해 보겠어요. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I don’t think I’ll be any good at tennis, but I’ll give it a try. 발음

examples.korean: I don’t want to go to the party, but I suppose I’d better put in an appearance. 발음듣기 난 그 파티에 가고 싶지 않지만 잠깐 얼굴은 내밀어야 할 것 같다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I don’t want to go to the party, but I suppose I’d better put in an appearance. 발음

examples.korean: a steady trickle of visitors 발음듣기 많지는 않지만 꾸준히 이어지는[찾아오는] 방문객들 Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: a steady trickle of visitors 발음

examples.korean: I don’t like it, but I’ll let it pass. 발음듣기 난 그게 마음에 들지 않지만 반대하지는 않겠다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I don’t like it, but I’ll let it pass. 발음

examples.korean: I don’t want to take away from his achievements, but he couldn’t have done it without my help. 발음듣기 그의 공적을 깎아내리고 싶지는 않지만 내 도움이 없었다면 그는 그것을 하지 못했을 거예요. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I don’t want to take away from his achievements, but he couldn’t have done it without my help. 발음
